using C functions: strcpy, strncpy

## guideline
1. When copying strings, ensure that the actual copied length (including the terminating '\0') is less than or equal to the destination buffer size, and that the string is null-terminated to prevent buffer overflow.
2. Prefer safe functions such as strncpy, strlcpy (if available), or snprintf over strcpy. strcpy does not limit copy length; if strcpy must be used in special cases, ensure the source string length (including '\0') is less than the destination buffer size and boundary checks have been performed.

